<p id="_9ad7038d-3a71-41ed-a7a6-8030da74d918"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle></math></stem>(Yb<sup>+</sup>) <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>=</mo><mn>435517610.739688</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_fm"><mi mathvariant="normal">fm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem></p>
<p id="_6248d9ef-b6c2-44b5-ad63-17355aacbacf">with an estimated relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>.</p>
<p id="_e8e18517-e7b9-45f6-83ae-073b83fe2c82">This radiation is already endorsed by the CIPM as a secondary representation of the definition of the second.</p></clause>
